2026-06-24 05:45:31,529 DEBUG msg #7: UserMessage tool_result(toolu_01FE2U9QvPzQz7nHJdPHxLTZ): {"assignees":[],"body":"## Summary\n\nThe live-forecast integration (`run_forecast` → `LiveForecaster`) is **broken on the real (non-stub) path** by two confirmed RNG defects in the Dixon-Coles scoreline sampler and its wiring. Both were empirically reproduced. The cycle's headline deliverable — `worldcup-playoff forecast` producing live title odds — crashes and/or yields statistically biased odds. This is exactly the hazard raised in issue #19's review comment.\n\nThe defects are invisible to the current test suite because `tests/test_live_forecast.py` injects **stub** `group_simulator` / `knockout_simulator` callables, bypassing the real `_group_sim_fn` / `_knockout_sim_fn` adapters that wire in `ScorelineSampler`.\n\n## Defect 1 — `forecast` crashes: `ScorelineSampler` is not callable\n\n`simulation/live_forecast.py:175` builds `sampler = make_sampler(ab, pcfg)`, which returns a `ScorelineSampler` **instance** (`poisson.py:269-271`). It is then passed to `resolve_tie(..., sampler=sampler, ...)` (`live_forecast.py:161-162`), and `resolve_tie` invokes it as a callable: `h, a = sampler(home, away)` (`knockout.py:142`). But `ScorelineSampler` defines only `.sample(...)` — no `__call__` (`poisson.py:234-256`).\n\nReproduced:\n```\n>>> s = make_sampler(ab); s('A', 'B')\nTypeError: 'ScorelineSampler' object is not callable\n```\n\n`run_forecast` wraps only `_fetch_state_and_abilities` in `try/except` (`live_forecast.py:222-225`); `LiveForecaster.run(...)` is **outside** the guard, so this `TypeError` propagates through `run_forecast` to the `forecast` CLI command (`cli_cycle5.py:168`), which does not catch it. On the no-key default path (martj42 schedule present), the command crashes.\n\n## Defect 2 — group stage has zero Monte-Carlo variance (constant seed)\n\n`group_stage.py:167` calls `self._sampler.sample(f.home_team, f.away_team)` with **no `random_state`**. In `ScorelineSampler.sample` (`poisson.py:250-251`):\n```python\nseed = random_state if random_state is not None else self._cfg.random_seed  # → 42\nrng = np.random.default_rng(seed)                                            # re-seeded EVERY call\n```\nBecause abilities are fit once (so `mat` is fixed per fixture) and the seed is the constant `42` on every call, **every remaining group fixture draws the identical scoreline in all ~100k tournaments**. Reproduced:\n```\n8 draws for the same fixture (no random_state): all (3, 2) → ZERO VARIANCE\n```\nConsequence: qualification (the R32 field) is effectively deterministic across the whole Monte-Carlo run — the only between-sim variation comes from exact-tie coin-flips — so title odds are severely biased. Constructing a fresh `default_rng` per draw is also the likely cause of missing the seconds-to-minutes perf target at ~5M draws.\n\n## Recommended fix\n\nThread **one** `np.random.Generator` through an entire tournament's draws (advance it, never re-seed per draw), as proposed in the #19 comment:\n\n- Extend `ScorelineSampler` to accept an injected `np.random.Generator` (constructor or per-`sample` arg) and draw from it instead of `np.random.default_rng(seed)` on every call. Consider adding `__call__(home, away) -> tuple[int, int]` so it satisfies the `_Sampler` contract `resolve_tie` expects, or have the orchestrator pass `_make_sampler` (the already-correct rng-threaded closure at `knockout.py:90-100`).\n- In `_group_sim_fn` / `GroupStageSimulator`, pass the per-tournament generator into the sampler so group scorelines decorrelate across sims.\n- Keep deriving one child `Generator` per iteration from `np.random.SeedSequence(master).spawn(N)` (already done at `live_forecast.py:260-262`) for reproducible, decorrelated, parallel-safe streams.\n- Unify on a single `Generator` type so the #17 coin-flip (currently a `random.Random` bridged via `int(rng.integers(...))` at `live_forecast.py:201`) and #18 penalty rung share one stream.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `worldcup-playoff forecast` runs end-to-end on the no-key default path without raising (real adapters, not stubs).\n- [ ] `ScorelineSampler` draws advance a single injected `Generator`; repeated draws for the same fixture show non-degenerate variance.\n- [ ] Two `run_forecast(..., seed=S)` runs with the same seed produce **bit-identical** title odds; different seeds produce different odds.\n- [ ] New regression test exercises the **real** `_group_sim_fn` / `_knockout_sim_fn` adapters (or `run_forecast` with a tiny fitted ability set) and asserts: (a) no `TypeError`, (b) group-stage scorelines vary across simulations, (c) seed reproducibility.\n- [ ] Existing tests still pass; SOLID / clean-code limits respected.\n\n## Affected files\n- `worldcup_playoff/simulation/poisson.py` (`ScorelineSampler`)\n- `worldcup_playoff/simulation/live_forecast.py` (`_group_sim_fn`, `_knockout_sim_fn`, `_play_round`, `run_forecast` guard)\n- `worldcup_playoff/simulation/group_stage.py` (sampler call site)\n- `tests/test_live_forecast.py` (add real-adapter regression test)\n\nRouted from Phase 5 final review (Cycle 5).\n","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIFhg","name":"priority:high","description":"High priority","color":"FF0000"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACor95BA","name":"phase:fix","description":"Phase: fix (routed from final review)","color":"B60205"}],"milestone":{"number":5,"title":"Cycle 5 — Tournament Simulation & Full Pipeline","description":"Extend tournament simulator: ingest played WC2026 results as fixed, simulate remaining group matches (correct tiebreak rules: goal-diff, goals-for, head-to-head, coin-flip), resolve Round of 32 from standings, simulate knockout (extra time λ×0.33 → penalty coin-flip), run ~100k Monte Carlo → full title odds + per-round advancement for all 48 teams. Historical odds scraper (backtest baseline: de-vig WC2014/18/22 from archived sources, cache to CSV). Evaluation metrics: RPS (primary), log-loss, Brier on ti