1054 tests pass, zero failures. The warnings are harmless font-rendering notices from Hypothesis generating Unicode edge-case strings.

The fix was straightforward: `_stub_state` defaulted to `n_teams=8` while `_stub_forecaster._group_sim` returned 32 teams (`T0..T31`). The champion could be any of T0-T31, but `champion_counts` only had keys for T0-T7, causing the `KeyError`. The fix has two parts:

1. Changed `_stub_state` default to `n_teams=32` so all possible champions are in `champion_counts`.
2. Made `_stub_forecaster._group_sim` derive its team list from `state.standings` (rather than a hardcoded `range(n_teams)`) — this guarantees the group sim only returns teams that `_extract_all_teams` has already registered in `champion_counts`, regardless of what `n_teams` is.

Issue #24 is now complete: all three production fixes (poisson.py, group_stage.py, live_forecast.py) and all regression tests are green.
